AB  - With the development of ports towards automation and intelligence, the crane cab has been transferred from the terminal to the central control room. The operator can rely on the camera on the crane to monitor and control the crane's job site. But there's a delay in what they see on their computers. This delay is a big security concern. Now you need to do video delay detection. However, there is no such testing equipment on the market. Therefore, a software that uses optical character recognition (OCR) technology is developed to analyze the time delay. This data on latency contributes to the safety of the port terminal. © 2025 SPIE.
