AB  - This paper designs a port container intelligent dispatching system that integrates the Internet of Things technology, and constructs a system architecture including the perception layer, network layer, data processing layer and application layer. The system integrates RFID, GPS and video recognition modules, and combines edge computing with cloud collaboration strategies to achieve accurate identification of container status and dynamic optimization of task scheduling. In terms of scheduling strategy, this paper introduces a hybrid optimization method of A∗ and genetic algorithm to jointly optimize the path and operation sequence. Through real data sets and multi-condition simulation experiments, the designed system shows superior performance in recognition rate, response delay, resource utilization and robustness. The research results provide a feasible system solution and technical path for the construction of smart ports, which has important engineering application value and promotion prospects. © 2025 IEEE.
