AB  - The importance of international maritime transportation in global trade is self-evident. However, the increasing frequency of maritime trade has imposed greater demands on maritime supply chains. This study aims to investigate the efficient scheduling of multitier equipment in automated container terminals. An integrated model encompassing berths, container yards and transportation subsystems is considered. Owing to the complexity of the proposed model, a comprehensive optimisation framework is developed by combining mathematical optimisation and simulation optimisation methods, along with the application of self-adaptive theory, to achieve optimality for specific indicators in the model. Finally, numerical experiments using real-world data are conducted to verify the effectiveness of the proposed model and algorithm. Copyright © 2025 Inderscience Enterprises Ltd.
