AB  - This research examines current port operations that use Internet of Things (IoT) technologies for cargo container monitoring and vessel traffic counts. Effective port management is crucial for smooth commodities movement and congestion reduction as global commerce grows. Addressing these issues with IoT solutions is promising. It analyzes cargo container IoT sensors and devices for real-time location, condition, and security monitoring. These IoT-enabled containers provide port status data for better logistical planning and security. IoT devices are used to count and control vessel traffic in the research. Sensors and data analytics at important port locations provide real-time vessel tracking and traffic monitoring. This data improves safety and optimizes vessel traffic flow, lowering congestion and wait times. The pros and downsides of using IoT in port operations include data privacy, security, and infrastructure needs. Smart port technologies may enhance marine efficiency, cost savings, and sustainability. The IoT can revolutionize port operations, notably cargo container monitoring and vessel traffic counts. Port capacity, security, and the environmental and economic viability of worldwide trade may all be improved with the help of the IoT.  © 2024 IEEE.
